Introduction

Kim Namjoo is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and actress. She made her official debut on April 19, 2011 as the Lead Vocalist and Lead Dancer of the Girl Group APINK under Choi Creative Lab. She's also part of sub-unit 'Apink BnN' alongside fellow Apink member BOMI.

Namjoo has also ventured to acting in 2015 where she played the Main Role of the web-drama "Investigator Alice".

She made her Solo debut with the single album "Bird" on September 7, 2020.

Namjoo also made her debut as a musical actress in 2022 with the musical "Midnight Sun".
